---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Science Solved It"
  description="How we collect, use, and protect your data on Science Solved It."
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
    { name: 'Privacy', url: '/privacy/' }
  ]}
>
  <div class="container-narrow" style="padding:3rem 0">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p style="color:var(--text-muted)">Last updated: June 17, 2026</p>

    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Analytics data:</strong> Page views, device type, approximate location (via IP anonymization) — collected through Google Analytics 4.</li>
      <li><strong>Affiliate links:</strong> When you click an affiliate link, the merchant may set cookies to track the referral. We do not directly collect this data.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How We Use This Data</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Understand which content is most useful to our readers</li>
      <li>Improve our reviews and guides based on reader behavior</li>
      <li>Generate revenue through affiliate commissions (this funds our testing)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>We use:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Google Analytics 4</strong> — anonymized traffic analysis</li>
      <li><strong>Affiliate networks</strong> — Impact.com, Awin, CJ Affiliate, Amazon Associates</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Your Rights</h2>
    <p>You can opt out of Google Analytics by installing the <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout">Google Analytics Opt-Out Browser Add-On</a>.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Email: <a href="mailto:hello@sciencesolvedit.store">hello@sciencesolvedit.store</a></p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
